===Etymology===
Middle English [[melodie]], borrowed from Old French [[melodie]], borrowed from Latin [[melodia]], borrowed from Greek [[μελῳδία]] (melōidia) "singing, chanting", derived from [[μέλος]] (melos) "musical phrase" + [[ἀοιδή]] (aoidē)  "song", contracted form [[ᾠδή]] (ōdē).

